        "step": 6,
        "type": "text",
        "text": "⭐ Your **Starfish Blink Circuit** is ready! Here's a summary:\n\n---\n\n### 🌟 Starfish Shape (6 LEDs)\n```\n           [ Top Arm ]\n  [Left-Up]  [CENTER]  [Right-Up]\n  [Left-Dn]            [Right-Dn]\n```\n\n| LED | Role |\n|-----|------|\n| LED Center | Body of the starfish |\n| LED Arm Top | Top arm |\n| LED Arm Right-Up | Upper-right arm |\n| LED Arm Right-Down | Lower-right arm |\n| LED Arm Left-Down | Lower-left arm |\n| LED Arm Left-Up | Upper-left arm |\n\n---\n\n### ⚡ How It Works\n- All **6 orange LEDs** are wired in parallel to **Pin 8**\n- Each LED has its own **220Ω resistor** for protection\n- They all **blink together** — ON for 600ms, OFF for 400ms\n- A single `digitalWrite(8, HIGH/LOW)` controls the whole starfish at once\n\n### 🎨 To customize:\n- **Speed up** blinking → reduce `delay(600)` / `delay(400)`\n- **Pulse effect** → switch pin 8 to PWM (pin 9) and use `analogWrite()`\n- **Wave effect** → wire each arm to a separate pin and stagger the blinks"
